      <div class="msgContentFrame">Karma system reminds me a lot of High School.  Two different people can make the exact same post but one will be rated to sub default, the other excellent.  It is just a big popularity contest.  It does have some good points.  Being able to rate people down who post false information, spam, something illegal, stuff completely off topic, etc.  But other times people simply disagree with something you say and rank you down when you don't really deserve it.  The Everquest 1 forums would have to be the worst for this actually here on Zam.  You do a 2 hour long quest for a rusty weapon (something you can loot within about 2 minutes of killing lvl 1 trash) you better not dare say it was a waste of your time or hint in any way you didn't like it. <br /> <br />I doubt they will let you rate down the blues.  Even if you could I doubt they would care.  I guarantee the blue who posted the &quot;Sorry your screwed&quot; response to the lost enchants during 4.0 would have been sub default in a matter of minutes.</div>
